    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Big-Omega (Ω) Notation Explained</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            line-height: 1.6;\n            max-width: 900px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            color: #333;\n        }\n        h1 {\n            color: #2c3e50;\n            text-align: center;\n        }\n        .definition {\n            background-color: #f8f9fa;\n            padding: 15px;\n            border-left: 4px solid #3498db;\n            margin: 20px 0;\n        }\n        .example {\n            background-color: #eaf7ff;\n            padding: 15px;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            margin: 20px 0;\n        }\n        .visualization {\n            height: 300px;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            margin: 20px 0;\n            position: relative;\n        }\n        .function-input {\n            display: flex;\n            gap: 10px;\n            margin: 20px 0;\n            align-items: center;\n        }\n        input, select, button {\n            padding: 8px;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n        }\n        button {\n            background-color: #3498db;\n            color: white;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            border: none;\n        }\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: #2980b9;\n        }\n        .result {\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-top: 10px;\n        }\n        .plot {\n            position: absolute;\n            bottom: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n        }\n        .line {\n            position: absolute;\n            height: 2px;\n            background-color: black;\n            transform-origin: 0 0;\n        }\n        .algorithm-line {\n            background-color: #e74c3c;\n        }\n        .bound-line {\n            background-color: #2ecc71;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Big-Omega (Ω) Notation</h1>\n    \n    <div class=\"definition\">\n        <h2>Definition</h2>\n        <p><strong>Big-Omega (Ω) notation</strong> describes the <em>lower bound</em> of an algorithm's growth rate. It represents the minimum resources (time or space) an algorithm needs as the input size grows.</p>\n        <p>Mathematically, we say <em>f(n) = Ω(g(n))</em> if there exist positive constants <em>c</em> and <em>n₀</em> such that:</p>\n        <p><em>f(n) ≥ c·g(n)</em> for all <em>n ≥ n₀</em></p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"example\">\n        <h2>Common Examples</h2>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Linear search: Ω(1) - best case when item is first</li>\n            <li>Binary search: Ω(1) - best case when item is middle</li>\n            <li>Bubble sort: Ω(n) - when list is already sorted</li>\n            <li>Matrix multiplication: Ω(n²) - must touch all elements</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"visualization\" id=\"visualization\">\n        <div id=\"plot\" class=\"plot\"></div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"function-input\">\n        <label for=\"algorithm\">Algorithm:</label>\n        <select id=\"algorithm\">\n            <option value=\"n\">Linear - O(n)</option>\n            <option value=\"n^2\">Quadratic - O(n²)</option>\n            <option value=\"n^3\">Cubic - O(n³)</option>\n            <option value=\"2^n\">Exponential - O(2ⁿ)</option>\n            <option value=\"log n\">Logarithmic - O(log n)</option>\n            <option value=\"n log n\">Linearithmic - O(n log n)</option>\n        </select>\n        \n        <label for=\"bound\">Ω Bound:</label>\n        <select id=\"bound\">\n            <option value=\"1\">Constant - Ω(1)</option>\n            <option value=\"n\">Linear - Ω(n)</option>\n            <option value=\"n^2\">Quadratic - Ω(n²)</option>\n            <option value=\"log n\">Logarithmic - Ω(log n)</option>\n        </select>\n        \n        <button onclick=\"updatePlot()\">Visualize</button>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"example\">\n        <h2>Interactive Example</h2>\n        <p>Enter a function f(n) and its proposed Ω bound g(n) to check:</p>\n        \n        <div class=\"function-input\">\n            <span>f(n) =</span>\n            <input type=\"text\" id=\"f-input\" value=\"3n^2 + 2n + 5\" placeholder=\"e.g., 3n^2 + 2n + 5\">\n            \n            <span>g(n) =</span>\n            <input type=\"text\" id=\"g-input\" value=\"n^2\" placeholder=\"e.g., n^2\">\n            \n            <button onclick=\"verifyOmega()\">Verify Ω</button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div id=\"verification-result\" class=\"result\"></div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        // Initialize the plot\n        function initPlot() {\n            const plot = document.getElementById('plot');\n            plot.innerHTML = '';\n            \n            // Add x-axis\n            const xAxis = document.createElement('div');\n            xAxis.className = 'line';\n            xAxis.style.width = '100%';\n            xAxis.style.left = '0';\n            xAxis.style.bottom = '0';\n            plot.appendChild(xAxis);\n            \n            // Add y-axis\n            const yAxis = document.createElement('div');\n            yAxis.className = 'line';\n            yAxis.style.height = '100%';\n            yAxis.style.left = '0';\n            yAxis.style.bottom = '0';\n            plot.appendChild(yAxis);\n            \n            // Add labels\n            const xLabel = document.createElement('div');\n            xLabel.textContent = 'n (input size)';\n            xLabel.style.position = 'absolute';\n            xLabel.style.bottom = '-20px';\n            xLabel.style.right = '10px';\n            plot.appendChild(xLabel);\n            \n            const yLabel = document.createElement('div');\n            yLabel.textContent = 'Time Complexity';\n            yLabel.style.position = 'absolute';\n            yLabel.style.top = '10px';\n            yLabel.style.left = '10px';\n            plot.appendChild(yLabel);\n        }\n        \n        // Evaluate a mathematical function\n        function evaluateFunction(expr, n) {\n            try {\n                // Replace ^ with ** for exponentiation\n                expr = expr.replace(/\\^/g, '**');\n                // Replace log n with Math.log(n)\n                expr = expr.replace(/log\\s*n/g, `Math.log(${n})`);\n                // Replace n with the value\n                expr = expr.replace(/n/g, n);\n                // Evaluate safely\n                return eval(expr);\n            } catch (e) {\n                return NaN;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        // Update the plot based on selected functions\n        function updatePlot() {\n            const algorithm = document.getElementById('algorithm').value;\n            const bound = document.getElementById('bound').value;\n            \n            const plot = document.getElementById('plot');\n            plot.innerHTML = '';\n            initPlot();\n            \n            const maxN = 20;\n            const maxValue = 500;\n            const width = plot.offsetWidth;\n            const height = plot.offsetHeight - 20;\n            \n            // Plot algorithm\n            const algoPoints = [];\n            for (let n = 0; n <= maxN; n++) {\n                let value;\n                switch (algorithm) {\n                    case 'n': value = n; break;\n                    case 'n^2': value = n * n; break;\n                    case 'n^3': value = n * n * n; break;\n                    case '2^n': value = Math.pow(2, n); break;\n                    case 'log n': value = Math.log(n + 1); break;\n                    case 'n log n': value = n * Math.log(n + 1); break;\n                    default: value = n;\n                }\n                algoPoints.push(value);\n            }\n            \n            // Plot bound\n            const boundPoints = [];\n            for (let n = 0; n <= maxN; n++) {\n                let value;\n                switch (bound) {\n                    case '1': value = 1; break;\n                    case 'n': value = n; break;\n                    case 'n^2': value = n * n; break;\n                    case 'log n': value = Math.log(n + 1); break;\n                    default: value = n;\n                }\n                boundPoints.push(value);\n            }\n            \n            // Find scaling factor\n            const maxAlgoValue = Math.max(...algoPoints.filter(x => isFinite(x)));\n            const maxBoundValue = Math.max(...boundPoints.filter(x => isFinite(x)));\n            const scale = height / Math.max(maxAlgoValue, maxBoundValue, maxValue);\n            \n            // Draw algorithm line\n            for (let i = 1; i <= maxN; i++) {\n                if (!isFinite(algoPoints[i-1]) || !isFinite(algoPoints[i])) continue;\n                \n                const line = document.createElement('div');\n                line.className = 'line algorithm-line';\n                line.style.left = `${(i-1)/maxN * 100}%`;\n                line.style.bottom = '0';\n                line.style.width = `${1/maxN * 100}%`;\n                line.style.height = `${Math.max(1, (algoPoints[i] - algoPoints[i-1]) * scale)}px`;\n                line.style.transform = `rotate(${Math.atan2(algoPoints[i] - algoPoints[i-1], 1)}rad)`;\n                plot.appendChild(line);\n            }\n            \n            // Draw bound line\n            for (let i = 1; i <= maxN; i++) {\n                if (!isFinite(boundPoints[i-1]) || !isFinite(boundPoints[i])) continue;\n                \n                const line = document.createElement('div');\n                line.className = 'line bound-line';\n                line.style.left = `${(i-1)/maxN * 100}%`;\n                line.style.bottom = '0';\n                line.style.width = `${1/maxN * 100}%`;\n                line.style.height = `${Math.max(1, (boundPoints[i] - boundPoints[i-1]) * scale)}px`;\n                line.style.transform = `rotate(${Math.atan2(boundPoints[i] - boundPoints[i-1], 1)}rad)`;\n                plot.appendChild(line);\n            }\n            \n            // Add legend\n            const legend = document.createElement('div');\n            legend.style.position = 'absolute';\n            legend.style.top = '10px';\n            legend.style.right = '10px';\n            legend.style.backgroundColor = 'white';\n            legend.style.padding = '5px';\n            legend.style.border = '1px solid #ddd';\n            \n            const algoLegend = document.createElement('div');\n            algoLegend.innerHTML = `<span style=\"color: #e74c3c\">■</span> Algorithm: ${algorithm}`;\n            legend.appendChild(algoLegend);\n            \n            const boundLegend = document.createElement('div');\n            boundLegend.innerHTML = `<span style=\"color: #2ecc71\">■</span> Ω Bound: ${bound}`;\n            legend.appendChild(boundLegend);\n            \n            plot.appendChild(legend);\n            \n            // Check if the bound is valid\n            let isValid = true;\n            for (let n = 1; n <= maxN; n++) {\n                if (algoPoints[n] < boundPoints[n] * 0.5) { // Using c = 0.5 for visualization\n                    isValid = false;\n                    break;\n                }\n            }\n            \n            const resultDiv = document.createElement('div');\n            resultDiv.style.position = 'absolute';\n            resultDiv.style.bottom = '10px';\n            resultDiv.style.right = '10px';\n            resultDiv.style.backgroundColor = 'white';\n            resultDiv.style.padding = '5px';\n            resultDiv.style.border = '1px solid #ddd';\n            resultDiv.textContent = isValid ? \n                `Valid Ω relationship (with c=0.5)` : \n                `Not a valid Ω relationship (with c=0.5)`;\n            plot.appendChild(resultDiv);\n        }\n        \n        // Verify Ω relationship between two functions\n        function verifyOmega() {\n            const fInput = document.getElementById('f-input').value;\n            const gInput = document.getElementById('g-input').value;\n            const resultDiv = document.getElementById('verification-result');\n            \n            // Try to find a constant c and n0\n            let c = 1;\n            let n0 = 1;\n            let found = false;\n            \n            // Test increasing values of c\n            for (c = 0.1; c <= 10; c += 0.1) {\n                // Find the smallest n0 where f(n) >= c*g(n) for all n >= n0\n                let validForC = true;\n                n0 = 1;\n                \n                // Check for increasing values of n\n                for (let n = 1; n <= 100; n++) {\n                    const fVal = evaluateFunction(fInput, n);\n                    const gVal = evaluateFunction(gInput, n);\n                    \n                    if (isNaN(fVal) || isNaN(gVal)) {\n                        resultDiv.innerHTML = `Error evaluating functions at n=${n}. Check your syntax.`;\n                        return;\n                    }\n                    \n                    if (n >= n0 && fVal < c * gVal) {\n                        validForC = false;\n                        break;\n                    }\n                }\n                \n                if (validForC) {\n                    found = true;\n                    break;\n                }\n            }\n            \n            if (found) {\n                resultDiv.innerHTML = `f(n) = Ω(g(n)) is TRUE with c = ${c.toFixed(2)} and n₀ = ${n0}`;\n                resultDiv.style.color = 'green';\n            } else {\n                resultDiv.innerHTML = `f(n) = Ω(g(n)) is FALSE - no suitable c and n₀ found`;\n                resultDiv.style.color = 'red';\n            }\n        }\n        \n        // Initialize the page\n        window.onload = function() {\n            initPlot();\n            updatePlot();\n        };\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
